Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour half of the @boiled water{62%ml} into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine rice{150%g}, ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British beef mince{240%g} and green beans, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{}, mix together the @peanut butter{60%g}, @sweet chilli sauce{64%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and remaining @boiled water{63%ml} until smooth.

Add to the beef mince and simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Taste and season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if needed.

Share the rice between your bowls.

Top with the satay beef and beans.

Sprinkle over the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

Enjoy!

> Step X MOD: If you've chosen beef mince instead of pork, cook the recipe in the same way.